        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">The Fall-Winter 2025 edition of the Paris Fashion Week featured <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-15-03-2025-r3-4-exciting-designer-debuts?source=website" target="_blank">exciting designer debuts</a>, including Julian Klausner at Dries Van Noten, Sarah Burton at Givenchy, and Haider Ackermann at Tom Ford. The shows focused on escapism, empowerment, and playful style. Many designers are offering modern takes on office attire.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">Ackermann and Stella McCartney explored corporate fashion, while retro-inspired looks were seen at Valentino and Dries Van Noten. Alaïa and Marine Serre experimented with unique silhouettes. Issey Miyake celebrated the joy of dressing with modular designs. Miu Miu embraced vintage-inspired styles, while Saint Laurent used bold block colors. The season was filled with creativity, happiness, and fresh perspectives.</p>
        </mj-text>
